    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nOftentimes I'd like to `:checkhealth` and real quick make sure everything is alright.\n\nThe problem - `:checkhealth` is, assumedly, a blocking/synchronous operation, so scrolling down to view content already populated in the buffer is simply not possible.\n\nI know this isn't the most impactful feature (and perhaps a non-goal) but I'd like to start contributing to neovim. I consider this not too impossible of a first task but wanted to see if it was even desirable in the first place.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:checkhealth` is non-blocking (i.e. can scroll buffer as the content is populated)",
