        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@justinmk I believe the main issue is that the checks are blocking when they run. Currently, the checks run ieratively & synchronously [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/0d16260b49d4bb702027c998bbcf00c4ea94089f/runtime/lua/vim/health.lua#L429).\n\nI don't see an easy fix here to allow scrollability - the checks would have to be truly async, no?\n\nPerhaps overkill for a simple checkhealth buffer.\n\nIf you are aware of an easy way to update this health buffer in a truly non-blocking manner and believe this is worth the added complexity I will definitely implement - otherwise, feel free to close.",
